text: Tallabogue Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. It is a tributary to the Chickasawhay River. Tallabogue is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "palmetto creek". Variant names are "Taala Bogue Creek", "Talla Bogue Creek", "Talla Creek", "Tallobogue Creek", and "Tallow Bogue Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Clarke County, Mississippi
